01:08:05,520 --> 01:08:06,400
Each person has two chances.

1414
01:08:06,400 --> 01:08:07,080
From the chewy lemon drinks,

1415
01:08:07,080 --> 01:08:08,520
find the other person's
exclusive Chewer.

1416
01:08:08,520 --> 01:08:09,640
The loser will have a mouthful of lemon.

1417
01:08:09,920 --> 01:08:10,592
(Round 1)

1418
01:08:11,072 --> 01:08:12,240
(Sun Honglei's Chewer)

1419
01:08:12,240 --> 01:08:13,800
(Xingxu's random guessing)
Is it this one?

1420
01:08:15,196 --> 01:08:16,160
(Reading his expression)

1421
01:08:16,160 --> 01:08:16,800
No.

1422
01:08:17,984 --> 01:08:18,592
(Guessing again)

1423
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:19,640
(Congratulations, wrong again)
Still not.

1424
01:08:20,846 --> 01:08:21,408
(Don't celebrate too early)

1425
01:08:21,536 --> 01:08:22,752
(Round 2)

1426
01:08:23,136 --> 01:08:24,256
(Chen Xingxu's Chewer)

1427
01:08:24,448 --> 01:08:25,479
(Definitely winning)

1428
01:08:25,479 --> 01:08:25,920
This bottle?

1429
01:08:26,112 --> 01:08:27,104
(It's in the bag)

1430
01:08:27,392 --> 01:08:28,160
(Wrong guess)

1431
01:08:30,880 --> 01:08:31,600
This one should be it.

1432
01:08:32,800 --> 01:08:34,040
(Got it)
Your expression is different.

1433
01:08:34,040 --> 01:08:34,840
This is the one.

1434
01:08:34,840 --> 01:08:36,960
He is awesome.

1435
01:08:36,960 --> 01:08:38,720
Mainly because the chewing is genuine.

1436
01:08:39,080 --> 01:08:40,720
Lemon peel and pulp.

1437
01:08:41,160 --> 01:08:42,319
Sour, refreshing, and full of texture.

1438
01:08:42,319 --> 01:08:43,479
Very irresistible.

1439
01:08:44,832 --> 01:08:45,760
(Sour)

1440
01:08:46,120 --> 01:08:46,960
(Gloating)
So sour.

1441
01:08:47,840 --> 01:08:50,160
Yili Yoghurt Chewy Lemon is the best.

1442
01:08:50,160 --> 01:08:51,720
This is the lemon you can chew.

1443
01:08:51,720 --> 01:08:52,880
Drink and chew at the same time,

1444
01:08:52,880 --> 01:08:54,040
(Heart-thumping)
so irresistible you can't stop.

1445
01:08:54,040 --> 01:08:54,784
Don't stop.

1446
01:08:55,640 --> 01:08:57,024
Let's go take the helicopters.

1447
01:08:58,816 --> 01:09:02,040
(Please fasten your seatbelt
throughout the ride)

1448
01:09:02,040 --> 01:09:02,840
You're wearing too little.

1449
01:09:03,936 --> 01:09:04,608
(Concern from an elder)
You're wearing too little.

1450
01:09:04,608 --> 01:09:05,279
I have a thick coat.

1451
01:09:05,279 --> 01:09:05,640
You do?

1452
01:09:07,160 --> 01:09:08,279
You're wearing too little.

1453
01:09:08,279 --> 01:09:08,800
(Named again)

1454
01:09:08,800 --> 01:09:09,479
I have a coat.

1455
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:10,080
You have a leather jacket?

1456
01:09:15,160 --> 01:09:16,640
Your handbag is quite nice.

1457
01:09:17,720 --> 01:09:19,000
(Plush toy)
- A matching piece. - The coldest in winter...

1458
01:09:19,279 --> 01:09:19,640
(Squishing it flat)
It's cold.

1459
01:09:33,312 --> 01:09:35,136
(Face changes instantly)

1460
01:09:43,584 --> 01:09:44,920
So I've become a table, right?

1461
01:09:46,840 --> 01:09:48,120
You're a part of our playtime.

1462
01:09:51,635 --> 01:09:52,319
(Riding to the destination)

1463
01:09:52,319 --> 01:09:53,880
Can Lin Yi fly the plane?

1464
01:09:54,480 --> 01:09:55,680
He can fly. He has a license.

1465
01:09:56,480 --> 01:09:57,600
(Clip from Full Bloom)
You can fly it yourself?

1466
01:09:58,400 --> 01:09:58,840
I can.

1467
01:09:59,000 --> 01:10:00,840
You know all the buttons?

1468
01:10:01,080 --> 01:10:01,800
It's labeled:

1469
01:10:01,800 --> 01:10:04,000
which one's throttle
and which one's brake.

1470
01:10:05,200 --> 01:10:06,280
It's easier than driving a car.

1471
01:10:06,560 --> 01:10:06,920
Really?

1472
01:10:07,400 --> 01:10:08,520
The takeoff and landing are hard.

1473
01:10:09,400 --> 01:10:10,200
But once you're up,

1474
01:10:11,600 --> 01:10:12,360
you have no company.

1475
01:10:12,360 --> 01:10:12,760
So you just... yeah.

1476
01:10:12,760 --> 01:10:13,480
No matter how you fly,

1477
01:10:13,480 --> 01:10:15,328
you don't have to worry
about hitting anything.

1478
01:10:16,760 --> 01:10:18,080
Are you scared of taking a helicopter?

1479
01:10:19,520 --> 01:10:21,080
A helicopter?

1480
01:10:21,080 --> 01:10:21,440
No.

1481
01:10:21,840 --> 01:10:22,480
He's taken one before.

1482
01:10:22,480 --> 01:10:23,120
I've taken one before.

1483
01:10:26,000 --> 01:10:27,280
It has a bit of a Xinjiang vibe.

1484
01:10:27,616 --> 01:10:28,080
Yeah.

1485
01:10:31,400 --> 01:10:31,720
We're here.

1486
01:10:33,080 --> 01:10:33,408
So cool.

1487
01:10:33,408 --> 01:10:34,400
Not bad.

1488
01:10:38,360 --> 01:10:39,360
So cool.

1489
01:10:39,520 --> 01:10:40,360
So cool.

1490
01:10:40,360 --> 01:10:41,320
Too cool.

1491
01:10:44,840 --> 01:10:45,760
It's like Top Gun.

1492
01:10:46,880 --> 01:10:48,000
This is like a movie set.

1493
01:10:50,120 --> 01:10:50,960
So cool.

1494
01:10:51,560 --> 01:10:53,120
This is way too cool.

1495
01:10:56,240 --> 01:10:57,120
Do you want to take a photo?

1496
01:10:57,800 --> 01:10:58,080
Sure.

1497
01:10:59,120 --> 01:11:00,760
This is what I just bought.

1498
01:11:01,184 --> 01:11:01,960
(Sock Lord is back)

1499
01:11:01,960 --> 01:11:02,816
A new pet.

1500
01:11:03,800 --> 01:11:04,760
Very cool.

1501
01:11:06,560 --> 01:11:07,200
Take one for me too.

1502
01:11:07,640 --> 01:11:08,560
Just sold it

1503
01:11:08,560 --> 01:11:09,880
to a guy named Li Naiwen.

1504
01:11:41,600 --> 01:11:41,920
Come on.

1505
01:11:41,920 --> 01:11:42,520
Get on. Come on.

1506
01:11:43,280 --> 01:11:43,776
Get on.

1507
01:11:51,840 --> 01:11:53,000
So cool.

1508
01:11:54,920 --> 01:11:55,200
Hello?

1509
01:11:55,200 --> 01:11:56,560
Can you hear me, everybody?

1510
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:57,840
I can hear you.

1511
01:11:57,840 --> 01:11:58,360
I can hear you.

1512
01:11:58,840 --> 01:12:00,560
I've already learned
which buttons to press.

1513
01:12:02,640 --> 01:12:03,280
Don't scare me.

1514
01:12:03,520 --> 01:12:04,160
You'll fly it?

1515
01:12:06,000 --> 01:12:07,480
I remember I took one once.

1516
01:12:08,240 --> 01:12:08,680
I took one.

1517
01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:09,760
I took one in Xinjiang once.

1518
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:10,160
Really?

1519
01:12:11,103 --> 01:12:13,568
(Two helicopters are ready for takeoff)

1520
01:12:31,240 --> 01:12:32,480
We're up.

1521
01:12:41,120 --> 01:12:42,880
(The other helicopter
is ready for takeoff)

1522
01:12:49,472 --> 01:12:50,720
(Helicopter waver)
They're waving goodbye to us.

1523
01:13:00,920 --> 01:13:02,760
Yuwen, take a photo of them.

1524
01:13:03,776 --> 01:13:05,664
(Them on the other plane)

1525
01:13:28,800 --> 01:13:30,160
There are a lot of people
living down there.

1526
01:13:32,360 --> 01:13:33,160
It's a town.

1527
01:13:33,880 --> 01:13:34,160
Yes.

1528
01:13:36,480 --> 01:13:38,000
Hello, everyone.

1529
01:13:38,000 --> 01:13:39,880
(Hu Junxia, NZ-China Tourism President)
Today, we will take helicopters

1530
01:13:39,880 --> 01:13:42,440
to tour New Zealand's
world-famous geological wonder,

1531
01:13:42,440 --> 01:13:43,760
Milford Sound.

1532
01:13:43,760 --> 01:13:44,960
And we will stop

1533
01:13:44,960 --> 01:13:47,640
on the 10,000-year-old Bryant Glacier.

1534
01:13:58,480 --> 01:13:59,920
This lake is so blue.

1535
01:13:59,920 --> 01:14:00,560
Yeah.

1536
01:14:01,000 --> 01:14:03,440
(NZ's third-largest lake, on the South Island)
What we're seeing now is Lake Wakatipu.

1537
01:14:03,800 --> 01:14:05,520
(Longest lake, bolt-shaped, a must-see in Queenstown)
It's New Zealand's third largest lake.

1538
01:14:05,960 --> 01:14:07,640
It's a glacier-formed lake.

1539
01:14:08,280 --> 01:14:10,720
The water purity reaches 99.9%.

1540
01:14:11,080 --> 01:14:12,200
And there is a unique

1541
01:14:12,560 --> 01:14:13,360
seiche phenomenon.

1542
01:14:13,760 --> 01:14:16,360
The water surface rises and falls
rhythmically by about ten centimeters.

1543
01:14:16,360 --> 01:14:19,160
So it's also called
the "breathing lake" by locals.

1544
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:20,200
So beautiful.

1545
01:14:21,720 --> 01:14:24,440
The mountains surrounding the lake
are part of the Southern Alps.

1546
01:14:24,440 --> 01:14:27,240
The Remarkables peak nearby
rises to about 2,300 meters

1547
01:14:27,240 --> 01:14:28,840
and is a popular natural ski field.

1548
01:14:28,840 --> 01:14:30,720
After crossing this mountain,
we will soon arrive at

1549
01:14:30,720 --> 01:14:31,640
Milford Sound.

1550
01:14:32,040 --> 01:14:34,360
We have to cross this mountain.

1551
01:14:34,688 --> 01:14:36,320
(Heading to Milford Sound)

1552
01:14:36,320 --> 01:14:37,448
(Filmed under safety conditions)

1553
01:14:37,448 --> 01:14:40,096
(Intense weightlessness strikes)

1554
01:14:45,481 --> 01:14:46,720
(Calm)

1555
01:14:46,720 --> 01:14:47,760
So cool.

1556
01:14:48,120 --> 01:14:51,160
Ahead, we are about
to reach Milford Sound.

1557
01:14:52,360 --> 01:14:53,680
So beautiful.

1558
01:14:53,840 --> 01:14:56,560
This is the most spectacular fjord
in the Southern Hemisphere.

1559
01:14:56,560 --> 01:14:58,000
Tens of thousands of years ago,
during the Ice Age,

1560
01:14:58,360 --> 01:15:00,960
thick glaciers acted
like natural giant planers.

1561
01:15:01,400 --> 01:15:03,280
They slowly slid down
from the high mountains,

1562
01:15:03,760 --> 01:15:06,640
gradually scraping
the valleys deeper and wider

1563
01:15:06,640 --> 01:15:09,160
and forming the U-shaped valleys
of the present day.

1564
01:15:09,160 --> 01:15:10,360
When the glaciers retreated,

1565
01:15:10,360 --> 01:15:12,120
the low-lying valleys
were flooded by seawater,

1566
01:15:12,120 --> 01:15:14,200
becoming the fjord we see today.

1567
01:15:14,200 --> 01:15:15,920
The sea is over 400 meters deep
at its deepest point.

1568
01:15:15,920 --> 01:15:17,880
Milford Sound is exactly a masterpiece

1569
01:15:17,880 --> 01:15:19,320
of this geological evolution.

1570
01:15:19,800 --> 01:15:21,640
On sunny days,
it's fresh and picturesque.

1571
01:15:21,640 --> 01:15:24,640
And on rainy days, hundreds
of waterfalls gush from the cliffs,

1572
01:15:24,640 --> 01:15:25,920
creating a magnificent scene.

1573
01:15:26,720 --> 01:15:27,960
This waterfall is beautiful.

1574
01:15:27,960 --> 01:15:29,280
Stirling Falls, right?

1575
01:15:30,208 --> 01:15:31,808
(One of Milford Sound's
two most famous permanent falls)

1576
01:15:31,808 --> 01:15:33,080
(A massive torrent of water plunges down
from a cliff about 150 meters high)

1577
01:15:33,080 --> 01:15:35,400
Along the way, we can see
the approximately 150-meter-high

1578
01:15:35,400 --> 01:15:36,680
Stirling Falls.

1579
01:15:36,680 --> 01:15:37,600
It plunges straight down,

1580
01:15:37,600 --> 01:15:38,560
with a deafening roar,

1581
01:15:38,560 --> 01:15:39,600
and mist fills the air.

1582
01:15:41,000 --> 01:15:42,320
When you are in the fjord,

1583
01:15:42,320 --> 01:15:43,920
you feel like you are
both among the mountains

1584
01:15:43,920 --> 01:15:45,080
and over the ocean.

1585
01:15:45,080 --> 01:15:47,160
That's exactly why it's called a wonder.

1586
01:15:50,080 --> 01:15:51,000
Flying over the fjord,

1587
01:15:51,000 --> 01:15:53,000
we arrive at Bryant Glacier,

1588
01:15:53,000 --> 01:15:53,840
preparing to land.

1589
01:15:55,800 --> 01:15:56,880
So blue.

1590
01:15:56,880 --> 01:15:58,800
The glacier we are on now is called

1591
01:15:58,800 --> 01:15:59,680
Bryant Glacier,

1592
01:15:59,680 --> 01:16:01,680
a typical alpine cirque glacier.

1593
01:16:01,680 --> 01:16:04,640
It's surrounded by the steep cliffs
of the Humboldt Mountains.

1594
01:16:04,640 --> 01:16:05,840
The formation of glaciers

1595
01:16:06,320 --> 01:16:08,760
requires thousands of years
of snow compaction and crystallization.

1596
01:16:08,760 --> 01:16:09,760
The air is squeezed out,

1597
01:16:10,000 --> 01:16:12,280
eventually turning
into a blue-and-white,

1598
01:16:12,280 --> 01:16:13,280
extremely dense ice mass.

1599
01:16:13,600 --> 01:16:16,480
What's the difference between
glacier ice and snow on snowy mountains?

1600
01:16:16,480 --> 01:16:17,640
Although the glaciers

1601
01:16:17,840 --> 01:16:20,720
look like a solid white land,

1602
01:16:20,720 --> 01:16:23,400
they actually flow slowly every day,

1603
01:16:23,400 --> 01:16:25,280
just like a flowing

1604
01:16:25,280 --> 01:16:26,400
"river of time".

1605
01:16:27,560 --> 01:16:28,880
This is a small lake

1606
01:16:29,400 --> 01:16:31,000
formed by melting snow
on the mountaintop.

1607
01:16:33,376 --> 01:16:35,104
(Arriving at Bryant Glacier)

1608
01:16:36,560 --> 01:16:37,360
- We've landed.
- We've landed.

1609
01:16:40,440 --> 01:16:40,840
How is it?

1610
01:16:41,200 --> 01:16:41,696
Not bad.

1611
01:16:43,800 --> 01:16:44,400
Thank you.

1612
01:16:44,400 --> 01:16:45,160
Thank you.

1613
01:16:45,680 --> 01:16:47,160
What we are standing on

1614
01:16:47,160 --> 01:16:48,480
could be snow that fell

1615
01:16:48,480 --> 01:16:51,080
thousands of years ago,
or even longer ago.

1616
01:16:51,080 --> 01:16:52,760
It's snowing.

1617
01:16:53,160 --> 01:16:55,240
I hope we can all protect
the environment together

1618
01:16:55,240 --> 01:16:56,160
so that future generations

1619
01:16:56,160 --> 01:16:58,160
will still have the chance
to stand here.

1620
01:16:58,840 --> 01:17:00,240
Are we back in the Northeast?

1621
01:17:00,240 --> 01:17:03,760
♪The great Northeast is my hometown♪

1622
01:17:06,360 --> 01:17:07,280
I was really scared.

1623
01:17:07,280 --> 01:17:07,960
You were scared?

1624
01:17:07,960 --> 01:17:09,696
Then you should sit in the front row,
in the passenger seat.

1625
01:17:09,880 --> 01:17:10,600
Even more scared, right?

1626
01:17:11,120 --> 01:17:11,600
Even scarier.

1627
01:17:15,960 --> 01:17:16,720
Slow down.

1628
01:17:18,480 --> 01:17:19,640
Yuning, we Northeasterners

1629
01:17:19,640 --> 01:17:21,000
are not afraid of snow at all.

1630
01:17:21,480 --> 01:17:22,520
Yeah, what's there to be afraid of?

1631
01:17:23,520 --> 01:17:25,280
You look just like a bossy CEO.

1632
01:17:25,280 --> 01:17:26,240
You look so cool.

1633
01:17:26,240 --> 01:17:27,480
This helicopter looks like yours.

1634
01:17:28,000 --> 01:17:29,160
Is this yours?

1635
01:17:29,160 --> 01:17:29,720
Nice.

1636
01:17:29,720 --> 01:17:31,360
- A bossy Dandong CEO.
- In this outfit...

1637
01:17:31,360 --> 01:17:31,840
Absolutely cool.

1638
01:17:31,840 --> 01:17:32,160
You know what?

1639
01:17:32,160 --> 01:17:34,000
This outfit goes so well
with the helicopter.

1640
01:17:38,560 --> 01:17:39,560
Come on, let's take a group photo.

1641
01:17:39,560 --> 01:17:40,320
Group photo.

1642
01:17:41,360 --> 01:17:41,640
Oh no.

1643
01:17:41,640 --> 01:17:42,400
- Xingxu.
- Xingxu.

1644
01:17:42,400 --> 01:17:43,080
Jun is gone.

1645
01:17:43,480 --> 01:17:44,240
Who's taking the photo?

1646
01:17:44,240 --> 01:17:44,960
No one is holding the camera.

1647
01:17:44,960 --> 01:17:45,960
Xingxu.

1648
01:17:45,960 --> 01:17:46,480
Come on.

1649
01:17:46,480 --> 01:17:47,904
(New camera operator)

1650
01:17:49,160 --> 01:17:51,160
Three, two, one.

1651
01:17:54,080 --> 01:17:56,080
- Wow The World!
- Wow The World!

1652
01:17:56,080 --> 01:17:58,400
- Glacier ahead!
- Glacier ahead!

1653
01:17:58,976 --> 01:18:03,600
(Tip: Non-snow season. On snowy terrain,
keep voices low to prevent avalanches.)

1654
01:18:03,600 --> 01:18:04,680
Such strong penetration.

1655
01:18:04,920 --> 01:18:08,560
(Singing on the spot)
♪Children of the mountains♪

1656
01:18:10,520 --> 01:18:12,640
Gong Jun.

1657
01:18:13,920 --> 01:18:15,480
Let's shout together
on the count of three.

1658
01:18:15,480 --> 01:18:15,920
Okay.

1659
01:18:16,480 --> 01:18:17,840
One, two, three.

1660
01:18:18,440 --> 01:18:21,120
- Gong Jun.
- Gong Jun.

1661
01:18:22,520 --> 01:18:23,480
(Shouting across the distance)
Come back!

1662
01:18:24,680 --> 01:18:25,720
Gong Jun,

1663
01:18:26,120 --> 01:18:27,720
how are you?

1664
01:18:27,720 --> 01:18:29,280
I'm fine.

1665
01:18:33,400 --> 01:18:34,976
Honglei standing there is so funny.

1666
01:18:36,280 --> 01:18:37,240
He looks so tiny.

1667
01:18:37,760 --> 01:18:38,720
So crystal clear.

1668
01:18:40,600 --> 01:18:41,440
Let's make a diamond ring out of it.

1669
01:18:48,040 --> 01:18:49,960
Mountains hundreds
of millions of years old.

1670
01:18:49,960 --> 01:18:51,800
Snow tens of thousands of years old.

1671
01:18:52,400 --> 01:18:54,480
A blue lake, and...

1672
01:18:55,200 --> 01:18:57,248
(And a snowball)

1673
01:18:57,600 --> 01:18:58,200
And

1674
01:18:58,200 --> 01:18:59,320
a little rascal.

1675
01:19:00,400 --> 01:19:00,680
No.

1676
01:19:00,920 --> 01:19:01,560
No.

1677
01:19:02,160 --> 01:19:04,160
I didn't expect to throw it behind.

1678
01:19:05,160 --> 01:19:06,080
So cold.

1679
01:19:06,360 --> 01:19:07,616
